{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-entry-js","path":"/notes/py/iterators/product","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"itertools.product"},"html":"<h3><code class=\"language-text\">itertools.product(*itr, repeat=1)</code></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">product</code> function is used to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cycle through each element of each iterable</li>\n<li>Perform a cartesian product of input iterables</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>These iterables are based on the <code class=\"language-text\">*itr</code> parameter</li>\n<li>The number of repetitions is based on the <code class=\"language-text\">repeat</code> parameter</li>\n<li>The <code class=\"language-text\">repeat</code> parameter is optional and defaults to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">repeat</code> returns an iterator of elements that represent a cartesian product of the input iterables <code class=\"language-text\">itr</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Illustrating the <code class=\"language-text\">product</code> Function</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> itertools <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> product\n\n<span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> itr <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> product<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'ABC'</span><span cl